quran[42]{c,v,t}:
  80,1,He frowned and turned away
  80,2,that the blind man drew near him
  80,3,And what will cause thee to recognize so that perhaps he will purify himself
  80,4,or yet recollect and a reminder profit him
  80,5,But as for he who was self-complacent
  80,6,"then, thou hast attended to him"
  80,7,and not upon thee is any blame if he purifies not himself
  80,8,"Yet as for him who drew near to thee, coming eagerly for knowledge"
  80,9,and he dreads God
  80,10,"then, thou hast paid no heed to him"
  80,11,"No indeed! Truly, this is an admonition"
  80,12,"So let whoever willed, remember it"
  80,13,in scrolls to be held in esteem
  80,14,ones that are exalted and ones that are purified
  80,15,by the hands of generous writers
  80,16,"and ones who are kindly, generous"
  80,17,Perdition to the human being! How ungrateful he is
  80,18,From which thing did He create him
  80,19,"He created him from seminal fluid then, ordained that he be"
  80,20,He made the way easy for him again
  80,21,"Again, He caused him to die and be buried"
  80,22,"Again, when He willed, He will revive him"
  80,23,No indeed! The human being finishes not what He commanded him
  80,24,"Then, let the human being look on his foodâ€”"
  80,25,"how We, truly, unloosed rain water with a pouring out"
  80,26,"Again, We split the earth, a splitting"
  80,27,And We put forth in it grain
  80,28,and grapevines and reeds
  80,29,and olives and date palm trees
  80,30,and dense fertile gardens
  80,31,and sweet fruits and whatever grows on the earth
  80,32,an enjoyment for you and your flocks
  80,33,"Then, when the blare drew near"
  80,34,that Day a man will run away from his brother
  80,35,and his mother and his father
  80,36,and his companion wife and his children
  80,37,For every man of them on that Day will be a matter that will preoccupy him
  80,38,Faces that Day will be ones that are polished
  80,39,ones who are laugh and ones who rejoice at good tidings
  80,40,And faces on that Day will be dust-stained
  80,41,Gloom will come over them
  80,42,"Those, they are the ones who are ungrateful, ones who act immorally"